lem.Based on the plant shutdown stories told by over 130 industrial workers, and drawing on extensive archival and published sources, and songs and poetry from the time period covered, Steve High explores the central issues in the history and contemporary politics of plant closings. In so doing, this study poses new questions about group identification and solidarity in the face of often dramatic industrial transformation.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 21. Jun 2021) 0aDeindustrializationzLake StatesxHistory. 0aDeindustrializationzOntarioxHistory. 0aDisplaced workerszLakes StatesxSocial conditionsy20th century. 0aDisplaced workerszOntarioxSocial conditionsy20th century. 7aHISTORY / North America.2bisacsh40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781442620902423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9781442620902.jpg  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_HICS  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_HICS  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA5EBK